  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2019-07-23",
    "date": "2019-07-31T13:44:36Z",
    "text": "Research and Development Tax Credit Expansion Act of 2019\n\nThis bill\u00a0modifies the refundable research tax credit for new and small businesses to (1) increase the limit on refundability to $500,000, with an adjustment for inflation; (2) allow refundable amounts to cover all payroll taxes paid by such businesses; and (3) extend eligibility for the credit to small businesses with less than $10 million in gross receipts (currently, less than $5 million).\n\nThe bill also increases the rate of the alternative simplified tax credit for such businesses."
  },
